Rules of custom hooks:
  - Must start with "use" so React can enforce the rules of hooks.
  - Can call built-in hooks and other custom hooks.
  - Each call to a custom hook gets its own isolated state.

10. Rules of Hooks
------------------
1. Only call hooks at the top level — never inside loops, conditions, or nested
   functions. This ensures hooks are called in the same order on every render,
   which is how React associates hook state with a component.

2. Only call hooks from React function components or other custom hooks — never
   from regular JavaScript functions, class components, or event handlers.

The eslint-plugin-react-hooks package enforces both rules automatically.
